<span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span> RMB partnered with Afgri Group Holdings to create a first-of-its-kind infrastructure asset in the form of a grain storage investment platform. This innovative transaction, achieved in collaboration with leading South African institutional investors, creates a platform for future investment, growth and transformation in the agricultural sector. Acting as financial advisor, structurer, funder and funding arranger, RMB helped to unlock meaningful socio-economic value – increasing South Africa’s storage capacity potential and strengthening food security in the region. Moneyweb editor Ryk van Niekerk talks to David Jones and Philip de Villiers of RMB about this deal. Brought to you by Rand Merchant Bank (RMB).